                                                  written lines: 23 28; Uniform layout. Folio comes from a much smaller codex with a fragment of Psalm 119 (119:48-65) written in Sephardic square script. On the same folio, there is a partially erased Hebrew inscription in the upper margin.
Sometimes threefold catchwords for main text, Targum and commentary (e.g. ).
Watermark, , of a circle with the letters 'BG' and a cross on top, similar to 3046-3047 (dated 1569-71, Reggio Emilia).The end of a weekly section in the Pentateuch is marked by three letters pe; the beginning is distiguished by the large ornamental characters of the first word, together with a pen and ink design, usually of a dragon (similar larger design at the beginning of the book).The commentary is often arranged in ornamental designs of different kinds. Several additional or alternative Hafṭarot  given in the margins.
